{
  "_doc": "Multi-user enable profiles. install.hexa enables a plugin iff its tier is in the active profile's tier list (read from ~/.sidecar/profile, default 'full'), unless ~/.sidecar/plugin-overrides.json sets it explicitly. Tiers: core = universal safety/QoL/workflow (on for everyone) · hexa = needs the hexa-lang CLI or .hexa/.tape files (useless/blocking without it) · personal = dancinlab-specific governance/infra/style. A plugin with no tier here defaults to 'personal' (kept out of the minimal profile). Edit a tier to recategorize; this file is the classification SSOT, kept separate from marketplace.json on purpose.",
  "profiles": {
    "minimal": ["core"],
    "hexa": ["core", "hexa"],
    "full": ["core", "hexa", "personal"]
  },
  "default": "full",
